Plate-1.0.0-19-g6436d16
-----------------------

Plate is a tem(plate) engine that lets you load data from a CSV file into a
given template. Plate has the feature to load a source file and place the
templates after a specific line. Plate only supports CSV input data so in
order to use JSON data, you can use the included json2csv python script which
will convert JSON 2 CSV.

I build plate for my personal website. I rip my Github API data and use Plate
to display said data on my website. Generally Plate can be universal. Now, Plate will search through the given template, looking for a keyword
encapsulated within a specific prefix and suffix. The defaults in Plate are
"<!--$" and "-->" which, when applied to the template above, allows us to
locate and swap the "test" keyword. Plate will then search this keyword within
the header line of a given CSV file, if the keyword is found then plate will
replace the prefix + keyword + suffix with the value of the found data (Plate
runs over every row in a given CSV data file).

The -i and -t flags are very useful. The -i flag lets you specify a source
file and the -t flag lets you define a trigger inside the source file where
Plate will insert the generated templates.

Build Options:
--------------
Please read the Makefile for more information.

make [OPTIONS]
OPTIONS:
	.version  | Update the plate version (git based)
	plate     | Compile Plate
	clean     | Remove object files and build files
	install   | Install Plate globally
	uninstall | Uninstall plate globally
